{Even if Black manages to install his knight on d4, his problems are not
solved. This position is a typical example. White's thematic reaction would be
} 1. Nxd4 {It is very important to take with the knight. In this way, the
g2-bishop keeps pressing Black's queenside. The natural follow-up would be}
exd4 2. g4 $1 Bg6 3. Nc5 Bxc5 4. Rxc5 c6 5. Qd2 {[%csl Rc6,Rd4][%cal Gf1c1,
Gb3b4,Gb4b5,Gg2c6,Gc5c6,Gd2f4] A typical position in which White enjoys a
stable advantage due to the bishop pair and the vulnerable d4-pawn. White can
also increase the queenside pressure by means of Rfc1 followed by b3-b4-b5. On
the other hand, e2-pawn can be easily defended. Additionally, the g6-bishop is
out of play.} *

