{The setup with Be6 is rare but very ambitious. Black's plan is simple: Qd7,
0-0-0, h5,Bh3, etc... White needs to keep calm and not be afraid of ghosts.
The correct setup is: Bb2,Nc3,Rc1,Qc2,Rfd1 followed by Ne4-c5.} 8. Bb2 f6 9.
Nc3 $1 {With opposite castling White has no time for slow moves like d3.} Qd7
10. Rc1 O-O-O 11. Qc2 $1 (11. Ne4 {is premature due to 11...Bh3! with good
attacking chances for Black.}) 11... Kb8 {This prophylactic idea is the best
move for Black.} ({The immediate} 11... Bh3 {is not very good due to:} 12. Rfd1
{followed by d2-d4} Bxg2 13. Kxg2 h5 14. h4 $1 {Black has no attack and d2-d4
is coming}) *

