{After only 5 moves we reach the first critical position in this line. Black
has 3 ways to defend the pawn or can push 5...e4 I will try to explain to you
the pros and cons of all of them.} 5... Nc6 {Is Black's best option. White's
plan is to prepare slowly d4 utilizing 0-0, e3, etc...} (5... d6 {is allowing
White to play} 6. d4 $1 {with an advantage}) (5... e4 $5 {after this move we
need to remember the forced line} 6. Ng5 Bxf2+ $1 {the only move} 7. Kxf2 Ng4+
8. Kg1 Qxg5 9. Bxe4 {White's king is quite safe and White is better due to his
bishop pair.}) (5... Re8 $6 {Is just bad due to a typical tactic.} 6. Nxe5 $1)
*

