{[%evp 0,37,39,-24,-15,-15,-25,-25,18,-18,-45,-23,-30,-30,-30,-21,-58,-40,-35,
-20,-21,-5,16,10,10,10,10,1,1,-55,56,54,36,6,6,29,32,32,28,28]} 1. c4 e5 2. g3
Nf6 3. Bg2 c6 4. Nf3 e4 5. Nd4 d5 (5... Qb6 6. Nb3 a5 {looks somewhat
artificial, but it was played by many top players and must be seriously
considered.} (6... d5 7. cxd5 {tranposes to the text.}) 7. d3 a4 ({
Insufficient for equality is} 7... Bb4+ 8. Nc3 a4 9. Be3 Qd8 10. Nd4 a3 11. Qb3
Qa5 12. Bd2 axb2 13. Qxb2 exd3 14. exd3 {Black faced serious problems with
developing his queenside pieces in Renman, N - Nunn, J Eksjo 1981.}) 8. N3d2
Bc5 (8... d5 9. cxd5 {transposes to the mainline.}) 9. O-O e3 {The most
consistent. The control over the a7-g1 diagonal offers Black some stability.} (
{The tricky} 9... Bxf2+ $6 {quickly backfires:} 10. Rxf2 e3 11. Rxf6 $1 exd2+
12. Rf2 dxc1=Q 13. Qxc1 O-O 14. Nc3 d6 15. Ne4 $36 {The lack of development
makes Black's position very difficult.}) ({The timid} 9... exd3 $6 10. exd3 O-O
11. Nc3 Qa5 {is strongly met by} 12. d4 $1 Bxd4 13. Nb3 axb3 14. Qxd4 {White's
initiative clearly more than outweights the pawn.}) 10. fxe3 Bxe3+ 11. Kh1 Ng4
(11... O-O 12. Nc3 Ng4 {might lead to the same position.}) 12. Ne4 O-O 13. Nbc3
d5 {A pawn sacrifice to complete development as soon as possible.} ({The
immediate} 13... Bxc1 14. Qxc1 Ne3 $4 15. c5 {drops the piece.}) 14. cxd5 Bxc1
15. Qxc1 Ne3 16. Rf3 Nxg2 ({I've also examined} 16... Nxd5 17. Qc2 Bg4 (17...
a3 18. bxa3 Rxa3 19. Nxd5 cxd5 20. Ng5 $14) 18. Nxd5 cxd5 19. Rf4 Be6 20. Ng5
Nc6 21. Raf1 h6 22. Nxe6 fxe6 23. Qc1 $14 {White's bishop is superior to
Black's knight.}) 17. Kxg2 Qd8 {We have been following the top level game So,
W - Caruana, F Saint Louis 2019. Now White could have played} 18. dxc6 $146
Nxc6 19. Qg5 Nd4 20. Qxd8 Rxd8 21. Rf4 {, maintaining the extra pawn in an
excellent position.}) 6. cxd5 Qb6 (6... cxd5 $6 {is covered with 2...c6.}) 7.
Nb3 ({Less promising is} 7. Nc2 cxd5 8. d3 Nc6 9. Nc3 Be7 10. O-O O-O 11. dxe4
(11. Bg5 Rd8 12. dxe4 dxe4 13. Qc1 h6 14. Be3 Qa6 {Howell,D - Pert,N London
2016}) 11... dxe4 12. Ne3 Rd8 13. Ned5 Nxd5 14. Nxd5 Qc5 15. Bxe4 Be6 16. b4
Nxb4 17. Be3 Rxd5 18. Bxc5 Rxd1 19. Bxe7 Rxa1 20. Rxa1 {Chibukhchian, A -
Minasian, A Yerevan 2007} Bd5 $1 21. Bxd5 Nxd5 22. Bd6 Rc8 $11) (7. e3 $5 cxd5
8. d3 (8. O-O Nc6 9. d3 Bg4 10. Qa4 {Bourdonnais, L - Bakalarz, M Agneaux 2013}
exd3 $1 $15) 8... Bb4+ 9. Nc3 Nc6 10. O-O O-O 11. dxe4 Bxc3 12. bxc3 dxe4 $11 {
1-0 (32) Kenworthy, G (2275)-Briscoe, C (2210) Hertfordshire 1999}) 7... a5 {
This is a concrete way to exploit the drawbacks of the poor Nb3.} ({Dubious is
} 7... cxd5 $6 8. O-O Nc6 9. d3 Bf5 ({In comparison to 7.Nc2, after} 9... Be7
10. dxe4 dxe4 11. Nc3 O-O {White gains an important tempo with} 12. Be3 Qa6 13.
Nxe4 {, after which Black doesn't get any compensation for the pawn.}) 10. Be3
Qd8 {, as in Golubovic,B - Jakovljevic,V Teslic 2006 is bad in view of} 11. Nd4
Nxd4 12. Bxd4 exd3 13. exd3 Be7 14. Qb3 O-O 15. Qxb7 Bxd3 16. Rd1 {, and
White's positional advantage is decisive.}) 8. d3 {White has to play this to
vacate d2 for the knight.} a4 9. N3d2 exd3 (9... Bc5 $2 {is bad in view of} 10.
O-O Bxf2+ (10... e3 11. fxe3 Bxe3+ 12. Kh1 cxd5 13. Nc3 $16) 11. Rxf2 e3 12.
Rxf6 exd2+ 13. Rf2 dxc1=Q 14. Qxc1 O-O 15. Nc3 {White was already winning in
Cummings, D - Gurevich, A Toronto 2000.}) 10. O-O cxd5 ({The attempt to keep
the pawn structure more flexible with} 10... Nxd5 $6 11. Nc4 Qa6 {is playing
with fire:} 12. exd3 Be6 13. Re1 Be7 14. Rxe6 $1 fxe6 15. Qg4 {, with a
powerful attack.}) 11. exd3 Nc6 (11... Be7 {was once played by Fabiano, but it
doesn't have an independent value:} 12. Nc3 Qa5 13. Re1 Nc6 {with
transposition.}) 12. Nc3 Qa5 13. Re1+ Be7 14. b4 $1 {Only this allows White to
make use of his lead in development.} ({Less energetic is} 14. Nf3 O-O 15. Bd2
Qa6 16. Bg5 Be6 {Black solved all his problems in Navara, D - Caruana, F Saint
Louis 2017}) 14... axb3 15. Bb2 Qd8 ({After} 15... Bg4 16. Nxb3 Qd8 17. Qd2 O-O
18. Nb5 Qd7 19. a4 Bh3 20. Qf4 $14 {White retains some pressure due to his
powerful Bb2 and the control over d4.}) 16. Nxb3 O-O 17. h3 $1 {A decent
prophylactic move. Now Black's light-squared bishop will be rather passive on
e6.} Be6 18. Nb5 Re8 19. a4 {White had small but long-lasting positional
pressure in Ding Liren - Caruana, F internet 2019.} *

