{[%evp 0,1,2,-37]} {This position arises from the system when Black played 2...
c6 without including the moves 2...Nf6 3.Bg2. Now I suggest a different setup.
The move 6. e3 is still possible. Then after 6...Nf6 7.Bg2 we will transpose
to the previous chapter, but Black has a strong reply 6...Bc5! which seems to
solve the problems.} 6. Nc2 $1 {White's plan is similar to the one which we
saw before: Bg2, Nc3, d3, etc..., but in this line, we have an extra option to
play Ne3.} *

