{Positions like that are quite typical for the line with 2...c6. Black defends
the pawn on e4, therefore White has bishop pair and can start some active play
on the queenside. The game Aronian - Papaioannou continue:} 12. b4 $1 {Typical
plan in this position. White starts the "minority attack" and prepares Bb2.} *

